6. That none be queſtioned or moleſted for Matters of Conſcience and Religion; the grounds of implacable trouble, and the very ſpawn of Tyranny and Superſtition;
and that Tythes (ſprung from the ſame root, and tending to the ſame end, and to the obſtruction of Tillage and Induſtry) may alſo ceaſe, and no inforced maintenance
impoſed in the place thereof.
